<p><i><b>The Matrix</b></i> is a 1999 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Science_fiction_film" title=3D"Science fiction film">science fiction</a=
> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Action_film" title=3D"Action fil=
m">action film</a> written and directed by <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/The_Wachowskis" title=3D"The Wachowskis">the Wachowskis</a>.<sup i=
d=3D"cite_ref-Credited_1-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-Credited-1"><span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>[</span>a<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> It is the first i=
nstallment in the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix_(fran=
chise)" title=3D"The Matrix (franchise)"><i>Matrix</i> film series</a>, sta=
rring <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Keanu_Reeves" title=3D"Keanu=
 Reeves">Keanu Reeves</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laurenc=
e_Fishburne" title=3D"Laurence Fishburne">Laurence Fishburne</a>, <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carrie-Anne_Moss" title=3D"Carrie-Anne Mo=
ss">Carrie-Anne Moss</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hugo_Wea=
ving" title=3D"Hugo Weaving">Hugo Weaving</a>, and <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Joe_Pantoliano" title=3D"Joe Pantoliano">Joe Pantoliano</a=
>. It depicts a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dystopia" title=3D=
"Dystopia">dystopian</a> future in which humanity is unknowingly trapped in=
side the Matrix, a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Simulated_reali=
ty" title=3D"Simulated reality">simulated reality</a> created by <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Artificial_intelligence" title=3D"Artificial=
 intelligence">intelligent machines</a>. Believing computer hacker <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neo_(The_Matrix)" title=3D"Neo (The Matri=
x)">Neo</a> to be "the One" prophesied to defeat them, <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Morpheus_(The_Matrix)" title=3D"Morpheus (The Matrix)"=
>Morpheus</a> recruits him into a rebellion against the machines.
</p><p>Following the success of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bo=
und_(1996_film)" title=3D"Bound (1996 film)"><i>Bound</i></a> (1996), <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Warner_Bros." title=3D"Warner Bros.">Wa=
rner Bros.</a> gave the go-ahead for <i>The Matrix</i> after the Wachowskis=
 sent an edit of the film's opening minutes. Action scenes were influenced =
by <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anime" title=3D"Anime">anime</a=
> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Martial_arts_film" title=3D"=
Martial arts film">martial arts films</a>, particularly <a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fight_choreography" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Fi=
ght choreography">fight choreography</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Wire_fu" title=3D"Wire fu">wire fu</a> techniques from <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hong_Kong_action_cinema" title=3D"Hong Ko=
ng action cinema">Hong Kong action cinema</a>. Other influences include <a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allegory_of_the_cave" title=3D"Allego=
ry of the cave">Plato's cave</a>, 1990's <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Telnet" title=3D"Telnet">Telnet</a> hacker communities, and <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/William_Gibson" title=3D"William Gibson">=
William Gibson</a>'s <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cyberpunk" ti=
tle=3D"Cyberpunk">cyberpunk</a> novel <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Neuromancer" title=3D"Neuromancer">Neuromancer</a>. The film popularize=
d terms such as the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Red_pill" clas=
s=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Red pill">red pill</a> as well as a novel visual=
 effect known as "<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bullet_time" tit=
le=3D"Bullet time">bullet time</a>" in which a character's heightened perce=
ption is represented by allowing the action within a <a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Shot_(filmmaking)" title=3D"Shot (filmmaking)">shot</a> =
to progress in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Slow_motion" title=
=3D"Slow motion">slow motion</a> while the camera appears to move through t=
he scene at normal speed.
</p><p><i>The Matrix</i> opened in theaters in the United States on March 3=
1, 1999, to widespread acclaim from critics, who praised its innovative vis=
ual effects, action sequences, cinematography and entertainment value.<sup =
id=3D"cite_ref-RottenTomatoes_7-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-RottenTomatoes-7"><span class=3D"=
cite-bracket">[</span>6<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup =
id=3D"cite_ref-meta_8-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-meta-8"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</spa=
n>7<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The film was a box offic=
e success, grossing over $460 million on a $63 million budget, becoming the=
 highest-grossing Warner Bros. film of 1999 and the <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/1999_in_film" title=3D"1999 in film">fourth-highest-gross=
ing film of that year</a>. The film received nominations at the <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/72nd_Academy_Awards" title=3D"72nd Academy Aw=
ards">72nd Academy Awards</a> for <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Academy_Award_for_Best_Visual_Effects" title=3D"Academy Award for Best Visu=
al Effects">Best Visual Effects</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Academy_Award_for_Best_Film_Editing" title=3D"Academy Award for Best Fil=
m Editing">Best Film Editing</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Academy_Award_for_Best_Sound" title=3D"Academy Award for Best Sound">Best S=
ound</a> and Best Sound Effects Editing, winning all four categories. The f=
ilm was also the recipient of numerous other accolades, including <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BAFTA_Award_for_Best_Sound" title=3D"BAFT=
A Award for Best Sound">Best Sound</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/BAFTA_Award_for_Best_Special_Visual_Effects" title=3D"BAFTA Award =
for Best Special Visual Effects">Best Special Visual Effects</a> at the <a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/53rd_British_Academy_Film_Awards" tit=
le=3D"53rd British Academy Film Awards">53rd British Academy Film Awards</a=
>, and the Wachowskis were awarded <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Saturn_Award_for_Best_Director" title=3D"Saturn Award for Best Director">B=
est Director</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saturn_Award_=
for_Best_Science_Fiction_Film" title=3D"Saturn Award for Best Science Ficti=
on Film">Best Science Fiction Film</a> at the <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/26th_Saturn_Awards" title=3D"26th Saturn Awards">26th Saturn Aw=
ards</a>.
</p><p><i>The Matrix</i> is considered to be among the greatest science fic=
tion films of all time,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-heritage1_9-0" class=3D"referenc=
e"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-heritage1-=
9"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>8<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</sp=
an></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-autogenerated1_10-0" class=3D"reference"><=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-autogenerated1=
-10"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>9<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</=
span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-Genre's_Best_11-0" class=3D"reference"><=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-Genre's_Best-1=
1"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>10<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</s=
pan></a></sup> and in 2012, the film was selected for preservation in the U=
nited States <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Film_Registr=
y" title=3D"National Film Registry">National Film Registry</a> by the <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Library_of_Congress" title=3D"Library o=
f Congress">Library of Congress</a> for being "culturally, historically, an=
d aesthetically significant".<sup id=3D"cite_ref-NFR_12-0" class=3D"referen=
ce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-NFR-12"><=
span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>11<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span>=
</a></sup> The film's success led to two sequels by the Wachowskis, both re=
leased in 2003, <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix_Relo=
aded" title=3D"The Matrix Reloaded">The Matrix Reloaded</a></i> and <i><a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix_Revolutions" title=3D"The M=
atrix Revolutions">The Matrix Revolutions</a></i>. The <i>Matrix</i> franch=
ise was further expanded through the production of comic books, video games=
 and an animated <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anthology_film" t=
itle=3D"Anthology film">anthology film</a>, <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/The_Animatrix" title=3D"The Animatrix">The Animatrix</a></i>, =
with which the Wachowskis were heavily involved. The franchise has also ins=
pired books and theories expanding on some of the religious and philosophic=
al ideas alluded to in the films. A fourth film, titled <i><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix_Resurrections" title=3D"The Matrix Resu=
rrections">The Matrix Resurrections</a></i> and directed solely by <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lana_Wachowski" class=3D"mw-redirect" tit=
le=3D"Lana Wachowski">Lana Wachowski</a>, was released in 2021.
</p>
<meta property=3D"mw:PageProp/toc">
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Plot">Plot</h2><span class=
=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DThe_Matrix&amp;action=3Ded=
it&amp;section=3D1" title=3D"Edit section: Plot"><span>edit</span></a><span=
 class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>In 1999, in an unnamed city, Thomas Anderson, a computer programmer know=
n as "<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neo_(The_Matrix)" title=3D"N=
eo (The Matrix)">Neo</a>" in hacking circles, delves into the mystery of th=
e "Matrix", bringing him to the attention of hacker <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Trinity_(The_Matrix)" title=3D"Trinity (The Matrix)">Trin=
ity</a>. She tells him that the enigmatic <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Morpheus_(The_Matrix)" title=3D"Morpheus (The Matrix)">Morpheus</a>=
 can answer Neo's questions. At his workplace, Neo is pursued by <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Agent_(The_Matrix)" title=3D"Agent (The Matr=
ix)">Agents</a> led by <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Agent_Smith=
" title=3D"Agent Smith">Agent Smith</a>, while Morpheus, able to somehow ob=
serve their movements, guides him by phone, but Neo ultimately surrenders.
</p><p>The Agents interrogate Neo about Morpheus, but he refuses to coopera=
te. In response, they seal his mouth shut and implant a robotic tracking de=
vice in his abdomen. Neo awakens at home, believing the encounter to have b=
een a nightmare until Trinity and her allies remove the device and take him=
 to Morpheus. Morpheus offers Neo a choice: a red pill to uncover the truth=
 about the Matrix or a blue pill to return to his normal life. Taking the r=
ed pill, Neo awakens in the real world, submerged in a mechanical pod and c=
onnected to invasive cables. He sees countless humans similarly encased and=
 tended by machines before being ejected from the structure and rescued by =
Morpheus aboard the hovercraft <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Nebuchadnezzar_(The_Matrix)" title=3D"Nebuchadnezzar (The Matrix)">Nebuchad=
nezzar</a></i>.
</p><p>Morpheus reveals that the year is approximately 2199. In the 21st ce=
ntury, humanity lost a war against its artificially intelligent creations, =
leaving Earth a devastated ruin. Humans blackened the sky to deprive the ma=
chines of solar power, but the machines retaliated by creating vast fields =
of artificially grown humans, harvesting their bioelectric energy. To keep =
their captives pacified, they built the Matrix, a simulated reality modeled=
 on human civilization at its peak. The remaining free humans founded an un=
derground refuge called Zion, surviving on scarce resources. Morpheus and h=
is crew hack into the Matrix to liberate others, exploiting its rules to ga=
in superhuman abilities within it. Even so, they remain outmatched by the A=
gents=E2=80=94sentient programs that protect the system=E2=80=94and death i=
n the Matrix means death in the real world. Morpheus freed Neo because he b=
elieves him to be "the One", a prophesied figure destined to free humanity.
</p><p>The crew enter the Matrix to seek guidance from <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Oracle_(The_Matrix)" title=3D"The Oracle (The Matr=
ix)">the Oracle</a>, who foretold the coming of the One. She implies that N=
eo is not the One and warns him of an imminent choice between his life and =
Morpheus's. The crew are ambushed by Agents after being betrayed by Cypher,=
 a disillusioned crew member who longs to return to the virtual comforts of=
 the Matrix. Convinced of Neo's importance, Morpheus sacrifices himself to =
confront Smith and is captured. Meanwhile, Cypher exits the Matrix and begi=
ns disconnecting the others, killing them. Before he can kill Neo and Trini=
ty, Tank, a wounded crew member, regains consciousness, kills Cypher, and s=
afely extracts the survivors.
</p><p>Smith interrogates Morpheus to obtain access codes for Zion's mainfr=
ame, which would enable the machines to destroy the human resistance. Deter=
mined to rescue him, Neo reenters the Matrix with Trinity. They free Morphe=
us, who escapes the Matrix with Trinity, but Smith intercepts Neo. Realizin=
g his potential, Neo fights Smith as an equal and kills him. However, Smith=
 resurrects in a new body and kills Neo.
</p><p>In the real world, machines called Sentinels attack the <i>Nebuchadn=
ezzar</i>. Standing by Neo's body, Trinity confesses her love for him and r=
eveals that the Oracle prophesied she would fall in love with the One. In t=
he Matrix, Neo revives with the ability to perceive and manipulate its code=
. He effortlessly destroys Smith and escapes the Matrix just as the <i>Nebu=
chadnezzar</i><span class=3D"nowrap" style=3D"padding-left:0.1em;">'</span>=
s electromagnetic pulse disables the Sentinels. Later, within the Matrix, N=
eo communicates with the system, vowing to show humanity a world of limitle=
ss possibilities, before flying away.
</p>
