<span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</sp=
an><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DThe_Matrix&amp;a=
ction=3Dedit&amp;section=3D11" title=3D"Edit section: Home media"><span>edi=
t</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p><i>The Matrix</i> was released on <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/DVD-Video" title=3D"DVD-Video">DVD</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Laserdisc" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Laserdisc">Laserdisc<=
/a> in its original <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aspect_ratio" =
title=3D"Aspect ratio">aspect ratio</a> of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/2.39:1" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"2.39:1">2.39:1</a> on Septe=
mber 21, 1999, in the US from <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Warn=
er_Home_Video" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Warner Home Video">Warner Hom=
e Video</a> as well as in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aspect_r=
atio_(image)" title=3D"Aspect ratio (image)">1.33:1</a> aspect ratio in <a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hong_Kong" title=3D"Hong Kong">Hong K=
ong</a> from ERA Home Entertainment. It was also released on <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/VHS" title=3D"VHS">VHS</a> in both <a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fullscreen_(filmmaking)" class=3D"mw-redirect" =
title=3D"Fullscreen (filmmaking)">full screen</a> and <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Widescreen" title=3D"Widescreen">widescreen</a> formats=
 on <span class=3D"nowrap">December 7</span>, 1999.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Mojo=
_6-2" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matr=
ix#cite_note-Mojo-6"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<span class=3D"c=
ite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> After its DVD release, it was the first DVD=
 to sell more than one million copies in the US.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Million=
_sales_90-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/T=
he_Matrix#cite_note-Million_sales-90"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>=
89<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> By 2000, the film went on=
 to become the first to sell more than three million copies in the US.<sup =
id=3D"cite_ref-Influence_Screened_33-8" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-Influence_Screened-33"><span=
 class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>32<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a>=
</sup> At that point, it became the top-selling DVD release of all time, ho=
lding this record for a few months before being surpassed by <i><a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gladiator_(2000_film)" title=3D"Gladiator (20=
00 film)">Gladiator</a></i>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-91" class=3D"reference"><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-91"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>90<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>=
 By <span class=3D"nowrap">November 10</span>, 2003, one month after <i>The=
 Matrix Reloaded</i> DVD was released, the sales of <i>The Matrix</i> DVD h=
ad exceeded 30 million copies.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-92" class=3D"reference"><=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-92"><span clas=
s=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>91<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup=
> It then debuted on both VHS and DVD formats in the UK on <span class=3D"n=
owrap">November 29</span>, 1999. <i>The Matrix</i> sold more than 107,000 D=
VD copies in just two weeks, breaking <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Armageddon_(1998_film)" title=3D"Armageddon (1998 film)">Armageddon<=
/a></i><span class=3D"nowrap" style=3D"padding-left:0.1em;">'</span>s recor=
d for being the country's best-selling DVD title.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-93" cl=
ass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_=
note-93"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>92<span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">]</span></a></sup> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Ultimate_=
Matrix_Collection" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"The Ultimate Matrix Colle=
ction">The Ultimate Matrix Collection</a> was released on <a href=3D"https:=
