<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Thematic_analysis">Thematic=
 analysis</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-=
bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DTh=
e_Matrix&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D18" title=3D"Edit section: Themati=
c analysis"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</=
span></span></div>
<div class=3D"quotebox pullquote floatright" style=3D"width:33%; ;">
<blockquote class=3D"quotebox-quote left-aligned" style=3D"">
<p><i>The Matrix</i> is arguably the ultimate <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Cyberpunk" title=3D"Cyberpunk">cyberpunk</a> artifact.
</p>
</blockquote>
<div style=3D"padding-bottom: 0; padding-top: 0.5em"><cite class=3D"left-al=
igned" style=3D"">=E2=80=94<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/William=
_Gibson" title=3D"William Gibson">William Gibson</a><sup id=3D"cite_ref-wil=
liamgibson_141-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/The_Matrix#cite_note-williamgibson-141"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[<=
/span>140<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup></cite></div>
</div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
See also: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix_(franchise)#I=
nfluences_and_interpretations" title=3D"The Matrix (franchise)">The Matrix =
(franchise) =C2=A7&nbsp;Influences and interpretations</a>, and <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Wachowskis#Personal_lives" title=3D"The W=
achowskis">The Wachowskis =C2=A7&nbsp;Personal lives</a></div>
<p><i>The Matrix</i> draws from and alludes to numerous cinematic and liter=
ary works, and concepts from mythology, religion and philosophy, including =
the ideas of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Buddhism" title=3D"Bu=
ddhism">Buddhism</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Christianity=
" title=3D"Christianity">Christianity</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Gnosticism" title=3D"Gnosticism">Gnosticism</a>, <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hinduism" title=3D"Hinduism">Hinduism</a> and <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Judaism" title=3D"Judaism">Judaism</a>.=
<sup id=3D"cite_ref-142" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-142"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1=
41<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Film_and_television">Film a=
nd television</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsect=
ion-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=
=3DThe_Matrix&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D19" title=3D"Edit section: Fi=
lm and television"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-brack=
et">]</span></span></div>
<p>The pods in which the machines keep humans have been compared to images =
in <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metropolis_(1927_film)" titl=
e=3D"Metropolis (1927 film)">Metropolis</a></i>, and the work of <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/M._C._Escher" title=3D"M. C. Escher">M. C. E=
scher</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Luddism_143-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-Luddism-143"><span clas=
s=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>142<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></su=
p> A resemblance to the eerie worlds of Swiss artist <a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/H._R._Giger" title=3D"H. R. Giger">H. R. Giger</a> was a=
lso recognized.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-144" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-144"><span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">[</span>143<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"=
cite_ref-145" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
The_Matrix#cite_note-145"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>144<span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The pods can be seen in <i><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Welcome_to_Paradox" title=3D"Welcome to P=
aradox">Welcome to Paradox</a></i> Episode 4 "News from D Street" from a 19=
86 short story<sup id=3D"cite_ref-146" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-146"><span class=3D"cite-brac=
ket">[</span>145<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> of the same=
 name by <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andrew_Weiner_(writer)" t=
itle=3D"Andrew Weiner (writer)">Andrew Weiner</a> which aired on September =
7, 1998, on the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syfy_(TV_channel)"=
 class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Syfy (TV channel)">SYFY Channel</a> and has=
 a remarkably similar concept. In this episode the hero is unaware he is li=
ving in virtual reality until he is told so by "the code man" who created t=
he simulation and enters it knowingly. The Wachowskis have described <a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stanley_Kubrick" title=3D"Stanley Kubric=
k">Stanley Kubrick</a>'s <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2001:_=
A_Space_Odyssey_(film)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"2001: A Space Odysse=
y (film)">2001: A Space Odyssey</a></i> as a formative cinematic influence,=
 and as a major inspiration on the visual style they aimed for when making =
<i>The Matrix</i>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-ebert-wachowskis_147-0" class=3D"refe=
rence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-ebert-=
wachowskis-147"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>146<span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-148" class=3D"reference"><a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-148"><span clas=
s=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>147<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></su=
p><sup id=3D"cite_ref-Kubrick_149-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-Kubrick-149"><span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">[</span>148<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Revie=
wers have also commented on similarities between <i>The Matrix</i> and othe=
r late-1990s films such as <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stra=
nge_Days_(film)" title=3D"Strange Days (film)">Strange Days</a></i>, <i><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dark_City_(1998_film)" title=3D"Dark =
City (1998 film)">Dark City</a></i> and <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/The_Truman_Show" title=3D"The Truman Show">The Truman Show</a></i>=
.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-154" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-154"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>=
b<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The similarity of the film=
's central concept to a device in the long-running series <i><a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Doctor_Who" title=3D"Doctor Who">Doctor Who</a><=
/i> has also been noted. As in the film, the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Matrix_(Doctor_Who)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Matrix (Doct=
or Who)">Matrix</a> of that series (introduced in the 1976 serial <i><a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Deadly_Assassin" title=3D"The Deadly=
 Assassin">The Deadly Assassin</a></i>) is a massive computer system which =
one enters using a device connecting to the head, allowing users to see rep=
resentations of the real world and change its laws of physics; but if kille=
d there, they will die in reality.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-155" class=3D"referen=
ce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-155"><spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>153<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></=
a></sup> The action scenes of <i>The Matrix</i> were also strongly influenc=
ed by live-action films such as those of director <a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/John_Woo" title=3D"John Woo">John Woo</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_r=
ef-Wired_PK_Dick_156-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-Wired_PK_Dick-156"><span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">[</span>154<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The martial =
arts sequences were inspired by <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Fist_of_Legend" title=3D"Fist of Legend">Fist of Legend</a></i>, a critica=
lly acclaimed 1995 martial arts film starring <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Jet_Li" title=3D"Jet Li">Jet Li</a>. The fight scenes in <i>Fis=
t of Legend</i> led to the hiring of Yuen as fight choreographer.<sup id=3D=
"cite_ref-157" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/The_Matrix#cite_note-157"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>155<span cl=
ass=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-158" class=3D"re=
ference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-158"=
><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>156<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</sp=
an></a></sup>
</p><p>The Wachowskis' approach to action scenes drew upon their admiration=
 for <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anime" title=3D"Anime">Japane=
se animation</a> such as <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ninja_=
Scroll" title=3D"Ninja Scroll">Ninja Scroll</a></i> and <i><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Akira_(1988_film)" title=3D"Akira (1988 film)">Aki=
ra</a></i>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Wachowski_transcript_159-0" class=3D"referen=
ce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-Wachowski=
_transcript-159"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>157<span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Director <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Mamoru_Oshii" title=3D"Mamoru Oshii">Mamoru Oshii</a>'s 1995 animated =
film <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ghost_in_the_Shell_(1995_f=
ilm)" title=3D"Ghost in the Shell (1995 film)">Ghost in the Shell</a></i> w=
as a particularly strong influence;<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Wachowski_transcript=
_159-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Ma=
trix#cite_note-Wachowski_transcript-159"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</sp=
an>157<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> producer <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joel_Silver" title=3D"Joel Silver">Joel Silver=
</a> has stated that the Wachowskis first described their intentions for <i=
>The Matrix</i> by showing him that anime and saying, "We wanna do that for=
 real".<sup id=3D"cite_ref-silver-anime-1_160-0" class=3D"reference"><a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-silver-anime-1-160"=
><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>158<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</sp=
an></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-silver-anime-2_161-0" class=3D"reference">=
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-silver-anime-=
2-161"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>159<span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>]</span></a></sup> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mitsuhisa_Ishi=
kawa" title=3D"Mitsuhisa Ishikawa">Mitsuhisa Ishikawa</a> of <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Production_I.G" title=3D"Production I.G">Product=
ion I.G</a>, which produced <i>Ghost in the Shell</i>, noted that the anime=
's high-quality visuals were a strong source of inspiration for the Wachows=
kis. He also commented, "...<span class=3D"nowrap">&nbsp;</span>cyberpunk f=
ilms are very difficult to describe to a third person. I'd imagine that <i>=
The Matrix</i> is the kind of film that was very difficult to draw up a wri=
tten proposal for to take to film studios". He stated that since <i>Ghost i=
n the Shell</i> had gained recognition in America, the Wachowskis used it a=
s a "promotional tool".<sup id=3D"cite_ref-south_bank_show_162-0" class=3D"=
reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-so=
uth_bank_show-162"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>160<span class=3D"c=
ite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Literary_works">Literary wo=
rks</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracke=
t">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DThe_Matr=
ix&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D20" title=3D"Edit section: Literary work=
s"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></div>
<p>The film makes several references to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Lewis_Carroll" title=3D"Lewis Carroll">Lewis Carroll</a>'s <i><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alice%27s_Adventures_in_Wonderland" title=
=3D"Alice's Adventures in Wonderland">Alice's Adventures in Wonderland</a><=
/i>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Salon_review_124-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-Salon_review-124"><span =
class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>123<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a>=
</sup> Comparisons have also been made to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Grant_Morrison" title=3D"Grant Morrison">Grant Morrison</a>'s comic=
 series <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Invisibles" title=
=3D"The Invisibles">The Invisibles</a></i>, with Morrison describing it in =
2011 as "(it) seemed to me (to be) my own combination of ideas enacted on t=
he screen".<sup id=3D"cite_ref-supergods_163-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-supergods-163"><span=
 class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>161<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a=
></sup> Comparisons have also been made between <i>The Matrix</i> and the b=
ooks of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carlos_Castaneda" title=3D=
"Carlos Castaneda">Carlos Castaneda</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-164" class=3D"r=
eference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-164=
"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>162<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</s=
pan></a></sup>
</p><p><i>The Matrix</i> belongs to the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Cyberpunk" title=3D"Cyberpunk">cyberpunk</a> genre of science fiction=
, and draws from earlier works in the genre such as the 1984 novel <i><a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neuromancer" title=3D"Neuromancer">Neur=
omancer</a></i> by <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/William_Gibson"=
 title=3D"William Gibson">William Gibson</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-williamgib=
son_141-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The=
_Matrix#cite_note-williamgibson-141"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1=
40<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> For example, the film's u=
se of the term "Matrix" is adopted from Gibson's novel,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-=
Neuromancer_Natali_interview_165-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-Neuromancer_Natali_interview-165=
"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>163<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</s=
pan></a></sup> though <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/L._P._Davies=
" title=3D"L. P. Davies">L. P. Davies</a> had already used the term "Matrix=
" fifteen years earlier for a similar concept in his 1969 novel <i><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DThe_White_Room_(novel)&amp=
;action=3Dedit&amp;redlink=3D1" class=3D"new" title=3D"The White Room (nove=
l) (page does not exist)">The White Room</a></i> ("It had been tried in the=
 States some years earlier, but their 'matrix' as they called it hadn't bee=
n strong enough to hold the fictional character in place").<sup id=3D"cite_=
ref-166" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_M=
atrix#cite_note-166"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>164<span class=3D=
"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> After watching <i>The Matrix</i>, Gibson =
commented that the way that the film's creators had drawn from existing cyb=
erpunk works was "exactly the kind of creative cultural osmosis" he had rel=
ied upon in his own writing;<sup id=3D"cite_ref-williamgibson_141-2" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_not=
e-williamgibson-141"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>140<span class=3D=
"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> however, he noted that the film's <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gnosticism" title=3D"Gnosticism">Gnostic<=
/a> themes distinguished it from <i>Neuromancer</i>, and believed that <i>T=
he Matrix</i> was thematically closer to the work of science fiction author=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philip_K._Dick" title=3D"Philip K=
. Dick">Philip K. Dick</a>, particularly Dick's speculative <i>Exegesis</i>=
.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-williamgibson_141-3" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-williamgibson-141"><span c=
lass=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>140<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a><=
/sup> Other writers have also commented on the similarities between <i>The =
Matrix</i> and Dick's work;<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Wired_PK_Dick_156-1" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_not=
e-Wired_PK_Dick-156"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>154<span class=3D=
"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-167" class=3D"referenc=
e"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-167"><span=
 class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>165<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a=
></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-168" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-168"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[<=
/span>166<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> one example of suc=
h influence is a Philip K. Dick's 1977 conference, in which he stated: "We =
are living in a computer-programmed reality, and the only clue we have to i=
t is when some variable is changed, and some alteration in our reality occu=
rs".<sup id=3D"cite_ref-173" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-173"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</sp=
an>c<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Philosophy">Philosophy</h3>=
<span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</sp=
an><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DThe_Matrix&amp;a=
ction=3Dedit&amp;section=3D21" title=3D"Edit section: Philosophy"><span>edi=
t</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>In <i>The Matrix</i>, a copy of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Jean_Baudrillard" title=3D"Jean Baudrillard">Jean Baudrillard</a>'s philos=
ophical work <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Simulacra_and_Simu=
lation" title=3D"Simulacra and Simulation">Simulacra and Simulation</a></i>=
, which was published in French in 1981, is visible on-screen as <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Concealing_objects_in_a_book" title=3D"Conce=
aling objects in a book">"the book used to conceal</a> disks",<sup id=3D"ci=
te_ref-Jamie_Allen_174-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-Jamie_Allen-174"><span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">[</span>171<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"ci=
te_ref-Simulacra_42-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-Simulacra-42"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[<=
/span>41<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> and Morpheus quotes=
 the phrase "desert of the real" from it.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Poole_Baudrill=
ard_175-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The=
_Matrix#cite_note-Poole_Baudrillard-175"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</sp=
an>172<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> "The book was require=
d reading"<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Jamie_Allen_174-1" class=3D"reference"><a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-Jamie_Allen-174"><s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>171<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span>=
</a></sup> for the actors prior to filming.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Simulacra_42=
-2" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix=
#cite_note-Simulacra-42"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>41<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-176" class=3D"refer=
ence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-176"><s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>173<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span>=
</a></sup> However, Baudrillard himself said that <i>The Matrix</i> misunde=
rstands and distorts his work.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Poole_Baudrillard_175-1" =
class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cit=
e_note-Poole_Baudrillard-175"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>172<span=
 class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-177" class=3D=
"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-1=
77"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>174<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]<=
/span></a></sup> Some interpreters of <i>The Matrix</i> mention Baudrillard=
's philosophy to support their claim "that the [film] is an <a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allegory" title=3D"Allegory">allegory</a> for con=
temporary experience in a heavily commercialized, media-driven society, esp=
ecially in developed countries".<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Jamie_Allen_174-2" clas=
s=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_no=
te-Jamie_Allen-174"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>171<span class=3D"=
cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The influence of <i><a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrixial_Gaze" title=3D"The Matrixial Gaze">The Mat=
rixial Gaze</a></i>, the philosophical-psychoanalytical concept of <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bracha_L._Ettinger" title=3D"Bracha L. Et=
tinger">Bracha L. Ettinger</a> on the archaic matrixial space that resists =
the field of simulacra,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-178" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-178"><span class=3D"=
cite-bracket">[</span>175<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><su=
p id=3D"cite_ref-179" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-179"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>176<=
span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-180" clas=
s=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_no=
te-180"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>177<span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">]</span></a></sup> "was brought to the public's attention through the wri=
tings of art historians such as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gr=
iselda_Pollock" title=3D"Griselda Pollock">Griselda Pollock</a> and film th=
eorists such as Heinz-Peter Schwerfel".<sup id=3D"cite_ref-181" class=3D"re=
ference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-181"=
><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>178<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</sp=
an></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-Jamie_Allen_174-3" class=3D"reference"><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-Jamie_Allen-174"=
><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>171<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</sp=
an></a></sup> In addition to Baudrillard and Ettinger, the Wachowskis were =
also significantly influenced by <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/K=
evin_Kelly_(editor)" title=3D"Kevin Kelly (editor)">Kevin Kelly</a>'s <i><a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Out_of_Control:_The_New_Biology_of_M=
achines,_Social_Systems,_and_the_Economic_World" class=3D"mw-redirect" titl=
e=3D"Out of Control: The New Biology of Machines, Social Systems, and the E=
conomic World">Out of Control: The New Biology of Machines, Social Systems,=
 and the Economic World</a></i>, and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Dylan_Evans" title=3D"Dylan Evans">Dylan Evans</a>'s ideas on <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evolutionary_psychology" title=3D"Evolutiona=
ry psychology">evolutionary psychology</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Screenplay_1=
3-5" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matri=
x#cite_note-Screenplay-13"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>12<span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Philosopher <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/William_Irwin_(=
philosopher)" title=3D"William Irwin (philosopher)">William Irwin</a> sugge=
sts that the idea of the "Matrix" =E2=80=93 a generated reality invented by=
 malicious machines =E2=80=93 is an allusion to <a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Descartes" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Descartes">Descarte=
s</a>' "<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/First_Meditation" class=3D=
"mw-redirect" title=3D"First Meditation">First Meditation</a>", and his ide=
a of an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evil_demon" title=3D"Evil =
demon">evil demon</a>. The Meditation hypothesizes that the perceived world=
 might be a comprehensive illusion created to deceive us.<sup id=3D"cite_re=
f-Salon_philosophy_182-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-Salon_philosophy-182"><span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">[</span>179<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The sam=
e premise can be found in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hilary_P=
utnam" title=3D"Hilary Putnam">Hilary Putnam</a>'s <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Brain_in_a_vat" title=3D"Brain in a vat">brain in a vat</a=
> scenario proposed in the 1980s.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Salon_philosophy_182-1=
" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#c=
ite_note-Salon_philosophy-182"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>179<spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> A connection between the premis=
e of <i>The Matrix</i> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plato" =
title=3D"Plato">Plato</a>'s <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allego=
ry_of_the_Cave" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Allegory of the Cave">Allego=
ry of the Cave</a> has also been suggested. The allegory is related to Plat=
o's <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Theory_of_Forms" class=3D"mw-r=
edirect" title=3D"Theory of Forms">theory of Forms</a>, which holds that th=
e true essence of an object is not what we perceive with our senses, but ra=
ther its quality, and that most people perceive only the shadow of the obje=
ct and are thus limited to false perception.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Influence_S=
creened_33-9" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
The_Matrix#cite_note-Influence_Screened-33"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[<=
/span>32<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>The philosophy of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Immanuel_=
Kant" title=3D"Immanuel Kant">Immanuel Kant</a> has also been claimed as an=
other influence on the film, and in particular how individuals within the M=
atrix interact with one another and with the system. Kant states in his <i>=
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Critique_of_Pure_Reason" title=3D"=
Critique of Pure Reason">Critique of Pure Reason</a></i> that people come t=
o know and explore our world through synthetic means (language, etc.), and =
thus this makes it rather difficult to discern truth from falsely perceived=
 views. This means people are their own agents of deceit, and so in order f=
or them to know truth, they must choose to openly pursue truth. This idea c=
an be examined in Agent Smith's monologue about the first version of the Ma=
trix, which was designed as a human <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Utopia" title=3D"Utopia">utopia</a>, a perfect world without suffering an=
d with total happiness. Agent Smith explains that, "it was a disaster. No o=
ne accepted the program. Entire crops [of people] were lost." The machines =
had to amend their choice of programming in order to make people subservien=
t to them, and so they conceived the Matrix in the image of the world in 19=
99. The world in 1999 was far from a utopia, but still humans accepted this=
 over the suffering-less utopia. According to William Irwin this is Kantian=
, because the machines wished to impose a perfect world on humans in an att=
empt to keep people content, so that they would remain completely submissiv=
e to the machines, both consciously and subconsciously, but humans were not=
 easy to make content.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-183" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-183"><span class=3D"=
cite-bracket">[</span>180<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Religion_and_mythology">Rel=
igion and mythology</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?=
title=3DThe_Matrix&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D22" title=3D"Edit sectio=
n: Religion and mythology"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsecti=
on-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Andrew Godoski sees allusions to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Christ" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Christ">Christ</a>, including Neo'=
s "<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miraculous_births" title=3D"Mir=
aculous births">virgin birth</a>", his doubt in himself, the prophecy of hi=
s coming, along with many other <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ch=
ristianity" title=3D"Christianity">Christian</a> references.<sup id=3D"cite=
_ref-Influence_Screened_33-10" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-Influence_Screened-33"><span class=3D=
"cite-bracket">[</span>32<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Am=
ongst these possible allusions, it is suggested that the name of the charac=
ter <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trinity_(The_Matrix)" title=3D=
"Trinity (The Matrix)">Trinity</a> refers to Christianity's doctrine of the=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trinity" title=3D"Trinity">Trinit=
y</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-184" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-184"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</=
span>181<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> It has also been no=
ted that the character Morpheus paraphrases the Chinese <a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taoist" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Taoist">Taoist=
</a> philosopher <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zhuang_Zhou" titl=
e=3D"Zhuang Zhou">Zhuangzi</a> when he asks Neo, "Have you ever had a dream=
, Neo, that you were so sure was real? What if you were unable to wake from=
 that dream? How would you know the difference from the real world and the =
dream world?"<sup id=3D"cite_ref-185" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-185"><span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">[</span>182<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matrixism" title=3D"Matrixi=
sm">Matrixism</a> is a fan-based possibly satirical religion created as "th=
e matrix religion".<sup class=3D"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact" sty=
le=3D"white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wik=
ipedia:Citation_needed" title=3D"Wikipedia:Citation needed"><span title=3D"=
This claim needs references to reliable sources. (December 2025)">citation =
needed</span></a></i>]</sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Transgender_themes">Transge=
nder themes</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsectio=
n-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3D=
The_Matrix&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D23" title=3D"Edit section: Trans=
gender themes"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">=
]</span></span></div>
<p>Years after the release of <i>The Matrix</i>, both of the Wachowskis cam=
e out as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transgender" title=3D"Tra=
nsgender">transgender</a> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trans_wo=
man" title=3D"Trans woman">women</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-TransMasterpiece_1=
86-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matr=
ix#cite_note-TransMasterpiece-186"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>183=
<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The red pill has been liken=
ed to red <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Estrogen" title=3D"Estro=
gen">estrogen</a> pills.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Vulture_187-0" class=3D"referen=
ce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-Vulture-1=
87"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>184<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]<=
/span></a></sup> Morpheus's description of the Matrix creating a sense that=
 something is fundamentally wrong, "like a splinter in your mind", has been=
 likened to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gender_dysphoria" titl=
e=3D"Gender dysphoria">gender dysphoria</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Vulture_187=
-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix=
#cite_note-Vulture-187"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>184<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> In the original script, Switch was a w=
oman in the Matrix and a man in the real world, but this idea was removed.<=
sup id=3D"cite_ref-188" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-188"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>18=
5<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In a 2016 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GLAAD_Media_Award=
" title=3D"GLAAD Media Award">GLAAD Media Awards</a> speech, Lilly Wachowsk=
i said: "There's a critical eye being cast back on Lana and I's  [<i><a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sic" title=3D"Sic">sic</a></i>] work thr=
ough the lens of our transness. This is a cool thing because it's an excell=
ent reminder that art is never static."<sup id=3D"cite_ref-189" class=3D"re=
ference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-189"=
><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>186<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</sp=
an></a></sup> In 2020, Lilly said <i>The Matrix</i> was intended as an alle=
gory for gender transition, but that "the corporate world wasn't ready".<su=
p id=3D"cite_ref-trans-metaphor_190-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-trans-metaphor-190"><span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>187<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></s=
up> She said it was "all about the desire for transformation but it was all=
 coming from a closeted point of view", but that she did not know "how pres=
ent my transness was in the background of my brain" when the Wachowskis wer=
e writing it.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-trans-metaphor_190-1" class=3D"reference">=
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-trans-metapho=
r-190"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>187<span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>]</span></a></sup> In an interview with <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Variety_(magazine)" title=3D"Variety (magazine)">Variety</a></i> =
in 2020, Reeves said the idea that the Matrix was an allegory for transgend=
er identity "wasn't introduced to me when we started for production on the =
films."<sup id=3D"cite_ref-reeves'_awareness_191-0" class=3D"reference"><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-reeves'_awarenes=
s-191"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>188<span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Legacy">Legacy</h2><span cl=
ass=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DThe_Matrix&amp;action=3D=
edit&amp;section=3D24" title=3D"Edit section: Legacy"><span>edit</span></a>=
<span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Filmmaking">Filmmaking</h3>=
<span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</sp=
an><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DThe_Matrix&amp;a=
ction=3Dedit&amp;section=3D25" title=3D"Edit section: Filmmaking"><span>edi=
t</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Following <i>The Matrix</i>, films made abundant use of slow motion, spi=
nning cameras, and, often, the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bul=
let_time" title=3D"Bullet time">bullet time</a> effect of a character freez=
ing or slowing down and the camera dollying around them.<sup id=3D"cite_ref=
-Lane_City_of_God_77-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-Lane_City_of_God-77"><span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">[</span>76<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The ability=
 to slow down time enough to distinguish the motion of bullets was used as =
a central gameplay mechanic of several video games, including <i><a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Max_Payne_(video_game)" title=3D"Max Payne (=
video game)">Max Payne</a></i>, in which the feature was explicitly referre=
d to as "bullet time".<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Influence_BBC_192-0" class=3D"ref=
erence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-Influ=
ence_BBC-192"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>189<span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-193" class=3D"reference"><a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-193"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>190<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup=
> It was also the defining game mechanic of the game <i><a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Superhot" title=3D"Superhot">Superhot</a></i> and its=
 sequels. <i>The Matrix</i><span class=3D"nowrap" style=3D"padding-left:0.1=
em;">'</span>s signature special effect, and other aspects of the film, hav=
e been <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parody" title=3D"Parody">pa=
rodied</a> numerous times,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Influence_EW2_23-2" class=3D"=
reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-In=
fluence_EW2-23"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>22<span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">]</span></a></sup> in comedy films such as <i><a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deuce_Bigalow:_Male_Gigolo" title=3D"Deuce Bigalow: Ma=
le Gigolo">Deuce Bigalow: Male Gigolo</a></i> (1999),<sup id=3D"cite_ref-19=
4" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#=
cite_note-194"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>191<span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">]</span></a></sup> <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sca=
ry_Movie" title=3D"Scary Movie">Scary Movie</a></i> (2000),<sup id=3D"cite_=
ref-195" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_M=
atrix#cite_note-195"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>192<span class=3D=
"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Shrek" title=3D"Shrek">Shrek</a></i> (2001),<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Influenc=
e_BBC_192-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/T=
he_Matrix#cite_note-Influence_BBC-192"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span=
>189<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> <i><a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kung_Pow!_Enter_the_Fist" title=3D"Kung Pow! Enter the=
 Fist">Kung Pow! Enter the Fist</a></i> (2002),<sup id=3D"cite_ref-196" cla=
ss=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_n=
ote-196"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>193<span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">]</span></a></sup> <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lastikman=
_(2003_film)" title=3D"Lastikman (2003 film)">Lastikman</a></i> (2003); <i>=
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marx_Reloaded" title=3D"Marx Reloa=
ded">Marx Reloaded</a></i> in which the relationship between Neo and Morphe=
us is represented as an imaginary encounter between <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Karl_Marx" title=3D"Karl Marx">Karl Marx</a> and <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leon_Trotsky" title=3D"Leon Trotsky">Leon=
 Trotsky</a>;<sup id=3D"cite_ref-197" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-197"><span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">[</span>194<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>  and in vide=
o games such as <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conker%27s_Bad_=
Fur_Day" title=3D"Conker's Bad Fur Day">Conker's Bad Fur Day</a></i>.<sup i=
d=3D"cite_ref-198" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-198"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>195<spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> It also inspired films featurin=
g a black-clad hero, a sexy yet deadly heroine, and bullets ripping slowly =
through the air;<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Influence_EW2_23-3" class=3D"reference"=
><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-Influence_EW=
2-23"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>22<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]=
</span></a></sup> these included <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Charlie%27s_Angels_(2000_film)" title=3D"Charlie's Angels (2000 film)">Ch=
arlie's Angels</a></i> (2000) featuring <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Cameron_Diaz" title=3D"Cameron Diaz">Cameron Diaz</a> floating throug=
h the air while the cameras flo-mo around her; <i><a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Equilibrium_(film)" title=3D"Equilibrium (film)">Equilibriu=
m</a></i> (2002), starring <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Christi=
an_Bale" title=3D"Christian Bale">Christian Bale</a>, whose character wore =
long black leather coats like Reeves' Neo;<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Influence_BBC=
_192-2" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Ma=
trix#cite_note-Influence_BBC-192"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>189<=
span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> <i><a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Night_Watch_(2004_film)" title=3D"Night Watch (2004 film)">=
Night Watch</a></i> (2004), a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russ=
ia" title=3D"Russia">Russian</a> megahit heavily influenced by <i>The Matri=
x</i> and directed by <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Timur_Bekmam=
betov" title=3D"Timur Bekmambetov">Timur Bekmambetov</a>, who later made <i=
><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wanted_(2008_film)" title=3D"Want=
ed (2008 film)">Wanted</a></i> (2008), which also features bullets ripping =
through air; and <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inception" tit=
le=3D"Inception">Inception</a></i> (2010), which centers on a team of sharp=
ly dressed rogues who are able to enter other people's dreams by "wiring in=
". The original <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tron" title=3D"=
Tron">Tron</a></i> (1982) paved the way for <i>The Matrix</i>, and <i>The M=
atrix</i>, in turn, inspired <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disne=
y" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Disney">Disney</a> to make its own Matrix=
 with a <i>Tron</i> sequel, <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tro=
n:_Legacy" title=3D"Tron: Legacy">Tron: Legacy</a></i> (2010).<sup id=3D"ci=
te_ref-Influence_EW_199-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-Influence_EW-199"><span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">[</span>196<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Also, the =
film's lobby shootout sequence was recreated in the 2002 Indian action come=
dy <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Awara_Paagal_Deewana" title=
=3D"Awara Paagal Deewana">Awara Paagal Deewana</a></i>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-=
200" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matri=
x#cite_note-200"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>197<span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Choreographers_and_actors">=
Choreographers and actors</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D=
"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/inde=
x.php?title=3DThe_Matrix&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D26" title=3D"Edit =
section: Choreographers and actors"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-=
editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p><i>The Matrix</i> had a strong effect on action filmmaking in Hollywood.=
 The film's incorporation of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wire_=
fu" title=3D"Wire fu">wire fu</a> techniques, including the involvement of =
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fight_choreography" class=3D"mw-re=
direct" title=3D"Fight choreography">fight choreographer</a> <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yuen_Woo-ping" title=3D"Yuen Woo-ping">Yuen Woo-=
ping</a> and other personnel with a background in <a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Hong_Kong_action_cinema" title=3D"Hong Kong action cinema">=
Hong Kong action cinema</a>, affected the approaches to fight scenes taken =
by some subsequent Hollywood action films,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-xmen_201-0" c=
lass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite=
_note-xmen-201"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>198<span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">]</span></a></sup> moving them towards more Eastern approaches.<s=
up id=3D"cite_ref-Influence_Screened_33-11" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-Influence_Screened-33"><=
span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>32<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span>=
</a></sup> The success of <i>The Matrix</i> created high demand for those c=
horeographers and their techniques from other filmmakers, who wanted fights=
 of similar sophistication: for example, wire work was employed in <i><a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/X-Men_(film)" title=3D"X-Men (film)">X-=
Men</a></i> (2000)<sup id=3D"cite_ref-xmen_201-1" class=3D"reference"><a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-xmen-201"><span cl=
ass=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>198<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></=
sup> and <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charlie%27s_Angels_(20=
00_film)" title=3D"Charlie's Angels (2000 film)">Charlie's Angels</a></i> (=
2000),<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Influence_EW_199-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-Influence_EW-199"><s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>196<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span>=
</a></sup> and Yuen Woo-ping's brother <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Yuen_Cheung-yan" title=3D"Yuen Cheung-yan">Yuen Cheung-yan</a> was cho=
reographer on <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Daredevil_(film)"=
 title=3D"Daredevil (film)">Daredevil</a></i> (2003).<sup id=3D"cite_ref-20=
2" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#=
cite_note-202"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>199<span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">]</span></a></sup> <i>The Matrix</i><span class=3D"nowrap" style=
=3D"padding-left:0.1em;">'</span>s Asian approach to action scenes also cre=
ated an audience for Asian action films such as <i><a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Crouching_Tiger,_Hidden_Dragon" title=3D"Crouching Tiger, =
Hidden Dragon">Crouching Tiger, Hidden Dragon</a></i> (2000) that they migh=
t not otherwise have had.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Influence_BBC_192-3" class=3D"=
reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-In=
fluence_BBC-192"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>189<span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Chad Stahelski, who had been a stunt double on <i>The Matrix</i> pri=
or to directing Reeves in the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John=
_Wick" title=3D"John Wick"><i>John Wick</i> series</a>, acknowledged the fi=
lm's strong influence on the <i>Wick</i> films,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-203" cla=
ss=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_n=
ote-203"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>200<span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">]</span></a></sup> and commented, "<i>The Matrix</i> literally changed t=
he industry. The influx of martial-arts choreographers and fight coordinato=
rs now make more, and are more prevalent and powerful in the industry, than=
 stunt coordinators. <i>The Matrix</i> revolutionized that. Today, action m=
ovies want their big sequences designed around the fights."<sup id=3D"cite_=
ref-204" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_M=
atrix#cite_note-204"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>201<span class=3D=
"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carrie-Anne_Moss" title=3D"=
Carrie-Anne Moss">Carrie-Anne Moss</a> asserted that prior to being cast in=
 <i>The Matrix</i>, she had "no career". It launched Moss into internationa=
l recognition and transformed her career; in a <i><a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/New_York_Daily_News" title=3D"New York Daily News">New York=
 Daily News</a></i> interview, she stated, "<i>The Matrix</i> gave me so ma=
ny opportunities. Everything I've done since then has been because of that =
experience. It gave me so much".<sup id=3D"cite_ref-cany_205-0" class=3D"re=
ference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-cany=
-205"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>202<span class=3D"cite-bracket">=
]</span></a></sup> The film also created one of the most devoted movie fan-=
followings since <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Star_Wars" tit=
le=3D"Star Wars">Star Wars</a></i>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Influence_EW2_23-4" =
class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cit=
e_note-Influence_EW2-23"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>22<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The combined success of the <i>Matrix<=
/i> trilogy, the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Lord_of_the_R=
ings_(film_series)" title=3D"The Lord of the Rings (film series)"><i>Lord o=
f the Rings</i> films</a> and the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Prequel_trilogy" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Prequel trilogy"><i>Star Wa=
rs</i> prequels</a> made Hollywood interested in creating trilogies.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-Influence_Screened_33-12" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-Influence_Screened-33"><span =
class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>32<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a><=
/sup> Stephen Dowling from the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BBC=
" title=3D"BBC">BBC</a> noted that <i>The Matrix</i><span class=3D"nowrap" =
style=3D"padding-left:0.1em;">'</span>s success in taking complex philosoph=
ical ideas and presenting them in ways palatable for impressionable minds m=
ight be its most influential aspect.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Influence_BBC_192-4=
" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#c=
ite_note-Influence_BBC-192"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>189<span c=
lass=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Cultural_impact">Cultural i=
mpact</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-brac=
ket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DThe_Ma=
trix&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D27" title=3D"Edit section: Cultural im=
pact"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span><=
/span></div>
<p><i>The Matrix</i> was also influential for its impact on <a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Superhero_films" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"S=
uperhero films">superhero films</a>. John Kenneth Muir in <i>The Encycloped=
ia of Superheroes on Film and Television</i> called the film a "revolutiona=
ry" reimagination of movie visuals, paving the way for the visuals of later=
 superhero films, and credits it with helping to "make <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Comic-book" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Comic-book"=
>comic-book</a> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Superheroes" class=
=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Superheroes">superheroes</a> hip" and effectively=
 demonstrating the concept of "faster than a speeding bullet" with its bull=
et time effect.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-206" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-206"><span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">[</span>203<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Adam Stern=
bergh of <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vulture.com" class=3D"=
mw-redirect" title=3D"Vulture.com">Vulture.com</a></i> credits <i>The Matri=
x</i> with reinventing and setting the template for modern superhero blockb=
usters, and inspiring the superhero renaissance in the early 21st century.<=
sup id=3D"cite_ref-207" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-207"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>20=
4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>One popular quote, "Guns. Lots of guns,"<sup id=3D"cite_ref-208" cla=
ss=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_n=
ote-208"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>205<span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-209" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-209"><span class=3D"=
cite-bracket">[</span>206<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> sp=
oken by Neo near the climax of the film, was incorporated into <i><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Wick:_Chapter_3_%E2%80%93_Parabellum=
" title=3D"John Wick: Chapter 3 =E2=80=93 Parabellum">John Wick: Chapter 3 =
=E2=80=93 Parabellum</a></i> as a line spoken by protagonist <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Wick_(character)" title=3D"John Wick (chara=
cter)">John Wick</a>, also played by Reeves.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-210" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_not=
e-210"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>207<span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-211" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-211"><span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">[</span>208<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The li=
ne was considered for use by screenwriters <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Patrick_Casey_(writer)" title=3D"Patrick Casey (writer)">Patrick C=
asey</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Josh_Miller_(filmmake=
r)" title=3D"Josh Miller (filmmaker)">Josh Miller</a> in the film <i><a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sonic_the_Hedgehog_3_(film)" title=3D"So=
nic the Hedgehog 3 (film)">Sonic the Hedgehog 3</a></i>, which starred Reev=
es as the voice of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shadow_the_Hedg=
ehog" title=3D"Shadow the Hedgehog">Shadow the Hedgehog</a>, but it was ult=
imately cut from that film's final script.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-212" class=3D=
"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-2=
12"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>209<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]<=
/span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-213" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-213"><span class=3D"cite-br=
acket">[</span>210<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Modern_reception">Modern re=
ception</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-br=
acket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DThe_=
Matrix&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D28" title=3D"Edit section: Modern re=
ception"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</spa=
n></span></div>
<p>In 2001, <i>The Matrix</i> placed 66th in the <a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/American_Film_Institute" title=3D"American Film Institute">A=
merican Film Institute</a>'s "<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/AFI%=
27s_100_Years...100_Thrills" title=3D"AFI's 100 Years...100 Thrills">100 Ye=
ars...100 Thrills</a>" list.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-AFIThrills_214-0" class=3D"=
reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-AF=
IThrills-214"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>211<span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">]</span></a></sup> In 2007, <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Entertainment_Weekly" title=3D"Entertainment Weekly">Entertainment Wee=
kly</a></i> called <i>The Matrix</i> the best science-fiction piece of medi=
a for the past 25 years.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Genre's_Best_11-1" class=3D"ref=
erence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-Genre=
's_Best-11"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>10<span class=3D"cite-brac=
ket">]</span></a></sup> In 2009, the film was ranked 39th on <i><a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Empire_(magazine)" title=3D"Empire (magazine)=
">Empire</a></i><span class=3D"nowrap" style=3D"padding-left:0.1em;">'</spa=
n>s reader-, actor- and critic-voted list of "The 500 Greatest Movies of Al=
l Time".<sup id=3D"cite_ref-215" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-215"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[=
</span>212<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> <i>The Matrix</i>=
 was voted as the fourth best science fiction film in the 2011 list <i>Best=
 in Film: The Greatest Movies of Our Time</i>, based on a poll conducted by=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_Broadcasting_Company" ti=
tle=3D"American Broadcasting Company">ABC</a> and <i><a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/People_(American_magazine)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=
=3D"People (American magazine)">People</a></i>. In 2012, the film was selec=
ted for preservation in the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nation=
al_Film_Registry" title=3D"National Film Registry">National Film Registry</=
a> by the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Library_of_Congress" tit=
le=3D"Library of Congress">Library of Congress</a> for being "culturally, h=
istorically, and aesthetically significant."<sup id=3D"cite_ref-NFR_12-1" c=
lass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite=
_note-NFR-12"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>11<span class=3D"cite-br=
acket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Red_pill_and_blue_pill">Red=
 pill and blue pill</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?=
title=3DThe_Matrix&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D29" title=3D"Edit sectio=
n: Red pill and blue pill"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsecti=
on-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Main article: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Red_pill_and_blue_pi=
ll" title=3D"Red pill and blue pill">Red pill and blue pill</a></div>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size mw-halign-right" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb">=
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Screenshot_from_1990_film_Tot=
al_Recall,_which_scholars_connect_to_The_Matrix.(1999).png" class=3D"mw-fil=
e-description"><img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/=
c/cf/Screenshot_from_1990_film_Total_Recall%2C_which_scholars_connect_to_Th=
e_Matrix.%281999%29.png/250px-Screenshot_from_1990_film_Total_Recall%2C_whi=
ch_scholars_connect_to_The_Matrix.%281999%29.png" decoding=3D"async" width=
=3D"250" height=3D"155" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-file-width=3D"401" d=
ata-file-height=3D"249"></a><figcaption>Scene from the 1990 film <i><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Total_Recall_(1990_film)" title=3D"Total =
Recall (1990 film)">Total Recall</a></i> where Dr. Edgemar (<a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roy_Brocksmith" title=3D"Roy Brocksmith">Roy Broc=
ksmith</a>) explains that swallowing a red pill is a "symbol of your desire=
 to return to reality"</figcaption></figure>
<p>Historians of film note that the trope of a "red pill" as decisive in a =
return to reality made its first appearance in the 1990 film <i><a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Total_Recall_(1990_film)" title=3D"Total Reca=
ll (1990 film)">Total Recall</a></i>, which has a scene where the hero (pla=
yed by <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arnold_Schwarzenegger" titl=
e=3D"Arnold Schwarzenegger">Arnold Schwarzenegger</a>) is asked to swallow =
a red pill in order to symbolize his desire to return to reality from a dre=
am-like fantasy.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-216" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-216"><span class=3D"cite-br=
acket">[</span>213<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D=
"cite_ref-217" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/The_Matrix#cite_note-217"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>214<span cl=
ass=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>The premise of <i>The Matrix</i> has been repurposed for multiple <a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conspiracy_theories" class=3D"mw-red=
irect" title=3D"Conspiracy theories">conspiracy theories</a> and <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alt-right" title=3D"Alt-right">alt-right</a>=
 fringe groups. For example, some online <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Men%27s_rights" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Men's rights">men's r=
ights groups</a> use the term "redpill" to mean men realizing that they are=
 supposedly being subjugated by feminism.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-218" class=3D"=
reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-21=
8"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>215<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</=
span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-219" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-219"><span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">[</span>216<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The term h=
as been used in discussion forums for right-wing topics such as <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gamergate_(harassment_campaign)" class=3D"mw-=
redirect" title=3D"Gamergate (harassment campaign)">Gamergate</a>, <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/White_supremacy" title=3D"White supremacy=
">white supremacy</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Incel" titl=
e=3D"Incel">incel</a> subculture and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/QAnon" title=3D"QAnon">QAnon</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-auto_220-0" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_not=
e-auto-220"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>217<span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">]</span></a></sup> As of 2021, the verb "pill" and suffix "-pilled" h=
ad entered more mainstream use and had come to mean developing a sudden int=
erest in something.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-auto_220-1" class=3D"reference"><a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-auto-220"><span c=
lass=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>217<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a><=
/sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Sequels_and_adaptations">Se=
quels and adaptations</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-=
editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.ph=
p?title=3DThe_Matrix&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D30" title=3D"Edit sect=
ion: Sequels and adaptations"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editse=
ction-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Main article: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix_(franchis=
e)" title=3D"The Matrix (franchise)">The Matrix (franchise)</a></div>
<p>The film's mainstream success led to the making of two sequels, <i><a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix_Reloaded" title=3D"The Matri=
x Reloaded">The Matrix Reloaded</a></i> and <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/The_Matrix_Revolutions" title=3D"The Matrix Revolutions">The M=
atrix Revolutions</a></i>, both directed by the Wachowskis. These were <a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Back_to_back_film_production" class=3D=
"mw-redirect" title=3D"Back to back film production">filmed back-to-back</a=
> in one <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Production_(film)" class=
=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Production (film)">shoot</a> and released on sepa=
rate dates in 2003.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-221" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-221"><span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">[</span>218<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The fi=
rst film's introductory tale is succeeded by the story of the impending att=
ack on the human enclave of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zion_(=
The_Matrix)" title=3D"Zion (The Matrix)">Zion</a> by a vast machine army.<s=
up id=3D"cite_ref-222" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-222"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>219=
<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-The_Matr=
ix_Reloaded_BBC_Review_223-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-The_Matrix_Reloaded_BBC_Review-223"><s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>220<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span>=
</a></sup>  The sequels also incorporate longer and more ambitious action s=
cenes, as well as improvements in bullet time and other visual effects.<sup=
 id=3D"cite_ref-The_Matrix_Reloaded_BBC_Review_223-1" class=3D"reference"><=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-The_Matrix_Rel=
oaded_BBC_Review-223"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>220<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-224" class=3D"refer=
ence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-224"><s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>221<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span>=
</a></sup>
</p><p>Also released was <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_An=
imatrix" title=3D"The Animatrix">The Animatrix</a></i>, a collection of nin=
e animated short films, many of which were created in the same <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anime" title=3D"Anime">Japanese animation</a> =
style<sup id=3D"cite_ref-The_Animatrix_IGN_Review_225-0" class=3D"reference=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-The_Animatr=
ix_IGN_Review-225"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>222<span class=3D"c=
ite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> that was a strong influence on the live act=
ion trilogy. <i>The Animatrix</i> was overseen and approved by the Wachowsk=
is, who only wrote four of the segments themselves but did not direct any o=
f them; much of the project was developed by notable figures from the world=
 of anime.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-The_Animatrix_IGN_Review_225-1" class=3D"refe=
rence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-The_An=
imatrix_IGN_Review-225"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>222<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In March 2017, Warner Bros. was in early stages of developing a rela=
unch of the franchise with <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zak_Pen=
n" title=3D"Zak Penn">Zak Penn</a> in talks to write a treatment and intere=
st in getting <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_B._Jordan" t=
itle=3D"Michael B. Jordan">Michael B. Jordan</a> attached to star. Accordin=
g to <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Hollywood_Reporter" ti=
tle=3D"The Hollywood Reporter">The Hollywood Reporter</a></i> neither the W=
achowskis nor Joel Silver were involved with the endeavor, although the stu=
dio would like to get at minimum the blessing of the Wachowskis.<sup id=3D"=
cite_ref-226" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
The_Matrix#cite_note-226"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>223<span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> On August 20, 2019, Warner Bros. Pic=
tures Group chairman <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toby_Emmerich=
" title=3D"Toby Emmerich">Toby Emmerich</a> officially announced that a fou=
rth Matrix film was in the works, with <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Keanu_Reeves" title=3D"Keanu Reeves">Keanu Reeves</a> and <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carrie-Anne_Moss" title=3D"Carrie-Anne Moss">C=
arrie-Anne Moss</a> set to reprise their roles as Neo and Trinity, respecti=
vely.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-227" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-227"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</s=
pan>224<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> <i><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix_Resurrections" title=3D"The Matrix Resur=
rections">The Matrix Resurrections</a></i> was released in theaters and on =
HBO Max on December 22, 2021.
</p><p>In September 2022, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Danny_Bo=
yle" title=3D"Danny Boyle">Danny Boyle</a> was announced to be directing an=
d producing a live immersive dance production of the film, entitled <i>Free=
 Your Mind</i>, which debuted in October 2023 at the <i>Aviva Studios</i> i=
n <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Manchester" title=3D"Manchester"=
>Manchester</a>, England.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-228" class=3D"reference"><a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Matrix#cite_note-228"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>225<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup=
>
</p>
